Items.Title: "Thornford Views"

42.65ha - 105ac

"Thornford Views" is located an easy 10 minute drive south of Goulburn and approx. 40 minute drive to Canberra on all sealed roads (including driveway).

A Large family home that is sure to impress with veranda's, Large full-length windows, wood fire and impressive and breathtaking valley views visible from every window in the property. This will most certainly be your rural escape that you've dreamt of.

All of the other bedrooms have built-ins and there will be no arguments over who chooses the biggest room as all of the bedrooms are generous and spacious in size.

A wonderful feature of "Thornford Views" is the enormous sun filled deck and entertaining area capturing the amazing country and district views
Heating and cooling are well catered for with zoned ducted reverse cycle air conditioning, as well as a slow combustion heater.

The homestead is generously serviced by rainwater storage of approx. 200,000 Litres

A massive American barn with power you will be the envy of all your friends.

Approximately 105 pasture improved acres of productive land suitable for any agricultural enterprise. Fantastic water for stock including 5 dams and topped off with a good set of cattle yards.

A stunning rural residence in a class of its own and positioned ideally for the Canberra or Goulburn commute.

This lovely home wont last long so be quick to inspect

Items.Title: ROSEHILL RETREAT

This remarkable, award winning, park like residence, is located within 5 minutes drive of the Goulburn post office. Rural aspects with city conveniences. This outstanding property offers the complete package - stunning architecturally designed home set amongst 10,200 meters squared of established, landscaped gardens hosting superb rural views in the background along with city convenience on your doorstep. 

Exceptionally private entertainers dream with an extraordinary high level of quality throughout, the home features 4 bedrooms and multiple living areas set over 3 levels with a separate studio offering guest or in-law accommodation, the perfect teenager's retreat or even the ultimate man cave. An inviting double sided fireplace features in two of the three lounge areas, plus reverse cycling throughout.

The home has been extensively renovated including the stunning kitchen with SMEG appliances, commercial flooring and 3 stylish bathrooms. There is an abundance of natural light and the brilliant Northly aspect has been used to great advantage capturing the art of the garden as additional living space within the house.

Outdoor entertaining has never been more superior and is catered for with a huge undercover area complete with built-in BBQ, bar fridge, daybed, remote weather blinds, two heat strips, overlooking a simply breath-taking infinity pool with extraordinary landscaping and rolling rural views.

Tuscan style sunken courtyard, complete with pizza oven along with shaded verandas and even a secret garden provide a number of exceptionally unique spaces that truly must been seen to be appreciated. An award winning garden in 2020 will be the pride of its new owners to exhibit. 

Enormous separate garages and gym facility complete with mezzanine storage, workshop and car accommodation.

The established park like grounds are well serviced by a bore and an extensive underground irrigation system and the delightful pond complete with "Monet's Bridge" which is a truly unique feature. Art brought to life in your own paradise. There is a solar powered water feature and a man-made creek with a multitude of wildlife, including kangaroos, ducks, kookaburras, black cockatoos, ibis, wrens and red faced finches. A nature lovers delight.

Self sufficiency has never been easier with a large vegetable patch. Herb beds. Fruit trees include figs, apples, pears, contained blackberries, strawberries. plum and cherry trees.

Security features include: security gates, security camera system, back to base alarm system.

If peace, privacy and serenity are paramount, where you can indulge in a sustainable life and have ample room to roam freely, this is the property for you.

Pest & Building Reports available on request.

What adds more to the character of the home is the second level which has the main bedroom, walk in robe and full en-suite. There is a study (or a 3rd living area as its big enough) off the main bedroom which has its own private balcony .
Step out to the meticulous backyard which has a resort style feel. There are catchment tanks to use for the veggie gardens. After a hard days work, relax and unwind in the spa which is nice and private.
